SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 686
By McNally
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Veterans of Foreign
Wars Post 5150 on the occasion of its eightieth
anniversary.
WHEREAS, on September 17, 1914, the Veterans of Foreign Wars of the United States
(VFW) was officially established with the set purpose to foster camaraderie among United
States veterans of overseas conflicts; serve veterans, the military, and communities across the
United States; and advocate on behalf of all veterans; and
WHEREAS, today, the Veterans of Foreign Wars of the United States is active in
communities at the international, national, State, and local levels with more than 2 million
members; and
WHEREAS, one distinguished chapter of the Veterans of Foreign Wars is VFW Post
5150 of Loudon, which is celebrating its eightieth anniversary on January 17, 2026; and
WHEREAS, since its inception, VFW Post 5150 has served veterans and their
immediate families, widows, and those veterans honorably discharged by providing various
services and opportunities to connect; and
WHEREAS, VFW Post 5150 strives to fulfill its mission to foster camaraderie among
United States veterans of overseas conflicts; to serve veterans, military, and community; and to
advocate on behalf of all veterans; and
WHEREAS, every American should express their appreciation for the honor, courage,
and bravery of United States veterans and for the service of the Veterans of Foreign Wars of the
United States; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor the Veterans of Foreign Wars Post 5150
